ace, conflict, and tension in Nagaland, Borderland Anxieties offers a window to understanding how gender, politics and anxiety intersect in a borderland state experiencing rapid social, political, and economic changes.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aGender identityzIndiazNāgāland. 0aSex rolexSocial aspectszIndiazNāgāland. 0aSex rolezIndiazNāgāland. 4aAsian Studies. 4aConflict and Peace. 4aDevelopment Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality Studies. 4aSociology and Social History. 4aSouth Asia. 7aHISTORY / Social History.2bisacsh  aMasculinity, Marginality, Borderland, Frontier, Zomia.1 aHarris, Tina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchendel, Willem, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311102374808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishz978311131913108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023z9783111318189oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048557035?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048557035423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048557035/original  a978-3-11-102374-8  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131913-1  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB